      "id": "t1",
      "content": "Key Circle Theorems:",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "t2",
      "content": "1. Angle at centre = 2 x angle at circumference (same arc)",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "t3",
      "content": "2. Angle in a semicircle = 90 degrees",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "t4",
      "content": "3. Angles in the same segment are equal",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "t5",
      "content": "4. Opposite angles of a cyclic quadrilateral sum to 180 degrees",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "t6",
      "content": "5. Tangent is perpendicular to the radius at point of contact",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "t7",
      "content": "Problem 1: Angle at centre theorem",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "t8",
      "content": "In a circle with centre O, the angle AOB at the centre is 124 degrees. Find the angle ACB at the circumference, where C is on the major arc.",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "m1",
      "content": "\\angle AOB = 124^\\circ, \\quad \\text{Find } \\angle ACB",
      "mode": "math",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "w1",
      "content": "",
      "mode": "math",
      "isProblem": false
    },
    {
      "id": "t9",
      "content": "Problem 2: Cyclic quadrilateral",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "t10",
      "content": "ABCD is a cyclic quadrilateral. Angle A = 85 degrees and angle B = 72 degrees. Find angles C and D.",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "m2",
      "content": "\\angle A = 85^\\circ, \\quad \\angle B = 72^\\circ",
      "mode": "math",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "w2",
      "content": "",
      "mode": "math",
      "isProblem": false
    },
    {
      "id": "t11",
      "content": "Problem 3: Tangent-radius theorem",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "t12",
      "content": "A tangent meets a circle at point P. The angle between the tangent and chord PQ is 35 degrees. Find the angle POQ at the centre.",
      "mode": "text",
      "isProblem": true
    },
    {
      "id": "m3",
      "content": "\\text{Angle between tangent and chord} = 35^\\circ",
      "mode": "math",
      "isProblem": true
